Drift intentionally provides no bulk reset. Every drifted edge must be individually reviewed and explicitly resolved. This friction is the core mechanism, not a limitation. A bulk reset would let an LLM blindly mark everything as reviewed without reviewing. The intended workflow — todo, diff --all, reset one edge at a time — forces attention at each edge. Removing this friction would make drift useless as a spec-code sync tool. See cli.no_bulk_reset for the CLI enforcement of this principle.